extendedInfo.description: With Mobile Banking from Five Star Bank you can easily bank anywhere at anytime whenever you like.*  Check your balances, pay bills (through optional bill payment), transfer money or locate ATM's and Five Star Bank branches.  Our Mobile Banking App is convenient, fast and free.FEATURES-     Review account balances-     Pay Bills**-     View recent transactions-     Transfer funds between linked Five Star Bank accounts**-     View Alerts-     Locate the nearest Five Star Bank ATM or branch by GPS locationMOBILE BANKING SECURITY-     You'll enjoy piece of mind knowing you have the same level of security as NetExpress Online Banking.-     The site uses SSL Encryption through VeriSign to help prevent unauthorized access-     Your user ID and password are required each time you log in.-     We are committed to protecting the privacy of your financial information.  See our online Privacy Policy at www.five-starbank.comFive Star Bank will not send unsolicited text or email messages containing urgent requests to contact the bank or ask for personal information.  Whenever communicating with the bank by phone, only use official Five Star Bank phone numbers published on your bank statement, the back of your check/debit card or on our web site at www.five-starbank.com.There is no fee from Five Star Bank.  Connectivity and usage rates may apply from your mobile carrier.*Must be enrolled in NetExpress Online Banking**Must have accounts and bill pay previously set-up in NetExpress Online BankingFive Star Bank Member FDIC

reviews.title: Poor
reviews.comment: Why do I have to put in ID number when logging in....who can remember that 12 digit number....should be able to just log in with my pass word..uninstalled
reviews.author: Patricia Avon

reviews.title: I like that FSB is catching up... but still behind
reviews.comment: It would be great if the app could remember my teller ID at least, maybe also my password.  This information is way too long to memorize.  If I have to constantly look my info up on my computer to use the app, then this app is worthless.

reviews.title: Works 40% of the time
reviews.comment: Its working a little better and for a while in the last month it has worked every day. But in the past week it will not let me see the account activity if it let\'s me log in at all. It seems that\'s there are still a lot of bugs to work out and a long way to come. But the good news is it\'s improving.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Four Months Later... Still Sucks
reviews.comment: Here we are, 4 months after my initial review... it still sucks, but not quite as badly.  It is functional, and it will do the job it is supposed to.  However, if you turn the screen while it is loading, it crashes.  You cannot exit the software with the menu or the <Back> key, and when you use <Home> to put it in the background, it crashes the next time you use it. I called Jack Henry & Associates today, and got voice mail - so I left a message, trying to be helpful... as an Android developer myself, I offered to give them my time for free to help debug the problems (I already know why they happen).  Not a call or a word in response from them.  So here is the bottom line: while the app is functional, I would not recommend it to anyone.  I would also not recommend Jack Henry to any bank who is looking for a banking app -- the company is not user-friendly, to say the least!! =================== Like Elizabeth, below, I tried to login using my NetTeller credentials -- and it promptly told me my account was not active.  However, it then locked up my phone -- I had to break to my Home screen and use \"Manage Apps\

reviews.comment: I was able to use it right away. I first had to login to netteller, go to options, mobile settings, and follow the steps to enable web access for mobile device. Once I did that I was ready to go. I hope this helps some people.

reviews.title: Does not work.
reviews.comment: I\'ve been waiting for this app for awhile and was excited to finally see it. However, I get the \"account not active\" message when I go to log in. I sent Five-Star a message several months ago asking what was wrong, and they said it was an internal software issue that they were working to fix. That was months ago, and it still isn\'t fixed. I finally just uninstalled it, after hopefully waiting this whole time. Don\'t waste your time, folks......it doesn\'t work.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Frustrating app
reviews.comment: Besides always having to put in too much info, most often it will not open the keyboard! The curser just blinks and no tapping in the world can get past it. The Generations bank app works GREAT!
